-- Egmont Signs $322 Million Revolving Credit Facility to Refinance
-- B y   S t e p h e n   M o r r i s
-- 2012-02-23T15:39:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/egmont-signs-322-million-revolving-credit-facility-to-refinance.html
Egmont International Holding A/S, a
closely held Danish media company and publisher, signed a 1.8
billion Danish kroner ($322 million) loan to refinance an
existing credit line.  The three-year revolving credit facility was provided
equally by Danske Bank A/S, which acted as agent, and Nordea
Bank AB, according to an e-mailed statement from lenders. Egmont
broadcasts television and publishes magazines and books in more
than 30 countries, and had revenue of about 1.4 billion euros in
2010, according to its  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Morris in London at 
